@NODE INTRODUCTION "Introduction"
October 1993 I bought my wonderful Korg 05R/W synthesizer module. Sound
was great, but it was hard to edit. After a couple of weeks I couldn't
stand it any longer and started programming an editor for it.
The result of this: an editor, a midimixer and a patchbay. It is all
very basic, but I'm still working on it. ( See @{" Future " link FUTURE} )

I hope you find it userful. If not please register it and tell me so!
(For example if you want this program supporting your synthesizer,
keyboard or module)
@ENDNODE

@NODE MIXER "The Midi Mixer"
The mixer consists of a 16-channel mixer with several functions.

  @{"  Meters      " link METERS}
  @{"  Edit Patch  " link PATCHEDIT}
  @{"  Levels      " link LEVEL-SLIDERS}
  @{"  Mute        " link MUTE}
  @{"  Solo        " link SOLO}

  @{"  Effects     " link EFF-EDIT}
  @{"  Patch Bay   " link PATCH-BAY}
  @{"  Voice List  " link VOICE-LIST}

  @{"  Menus       " link MIXER-MENUS}
@ENDNODE

@NODE METERS "The note level indicators"
The level indicators show the level of the notes going out of the
mixer. This can be notes played of the master-keyboard or played with
@{" Midi Play " link MIDI-PLAY}

When you're having an Amiga with a 68000 (Amiga 500, 500+, 600 or 2000)
go can gain speed by turning the level indicators off.
@ENDNODE

@NODE LEVEL-SLIDERS "The level sliders"
With the level sliders you can set the volume on a specific channel.
This doesn't work if your instument doesn't support control change
number 7 as volume change.
The level going out of the mixer can be seen on the @{" Meters " link METERS}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE SOLO "The Solo buttons"
The Solo button enables you to mute all channels except one. E.g. if you
press the Channel 5 Solo button, all channels will be muted except channel
5. This is convenient if you want to edit just one channel.
The functionality depends on what is specified in the @{ " Options/Mute-Solo Menu" link MUTESOLO}

See also @{" Mute " link MUTE}
@ENDNODE

@NODE MUTE "The Mute buttons"
The mute button enables you to mute a channel.
The functionality depends on what is specified in the @{ " Options/Mute-Solo Menu" link MUTESOLO}
Menu.

See also @{" Solo " link SOLO}
@ENDNODE

@NODE MIXER-MENUS "The Mixer Window Menus"
  @{"  Project  " link PROJECT}
  @{"  Options  " link OPTIONS}
  @{"  Filters  " link FILTERS}
@ENDNODE

@NODE PROJECT "The Project Menu"
  @{"  Open         " link OPENREG}
  @{"  Save         " link SAVEREG}
  @{"  Save as ...  " link SAVEASREG}

  @{"  About        " link ABOUT}

  @{"  Quit         " link QUIT}
@ENDNODE

@NODE OPENREG "Open a Registration"
This menu option opens a requester in which you can choose a registration
file in the form #?.reg.mid. All registrations file are in the Standard
Midi File format, so you can also 'Open' registrations by playing them
from a external midi file player.

NOTE: Unfortunately MidiPlay doesn't play System Exclusives at this
momnet, so the information stored SysEx format will not be set.
@ENDNODE

@NODE SAVEREG "Save a Registration"
This menu option saves the current registration to a Standard Midi File.
When the currect registration has no name, the @{" Save as ... " link SAVEASREG}
command will be called.
@ENDNODE

@NODE SAVEASREG "Save a Registration under a Name"
This menu option saves the current registration under a name in a Standard
Midi File.
A registration includes:
  - The Patch Bay settings (in SysEx format)
  - The Intrument selected on each channel (in SysEx format)
  - The Bank selected on each channel
  - The Voice selected on each channel
  - All Controller values (excluded are the RPN values)
@ENDNODE

@NODE QUIT "Quit"
The menu option closes all windows and terminates Master Midi. This may
also be achieved by clicking on the close-gadget of the Mixer Window.

All current window settings (place and size) and selected menu options
are saved in the tooltypes.
@ENDNODE

@NODE OPTIONS "The Options Menu"
  @{"  Mute/Solo Settings  " link MUTESOLO}
@ENDNODE

@NODE MUTESOLO "The Mute-Solo Prefences"
  @{"  Volume Zero   " link VOLZERO}
  @{"  Filter Notes  " link FILTNOTES}
  @{"  Filter All    " link FILTALL}
@ENDNODE

@NODE VOLZERO "Volume Zero"
Sets the volume of the instrument to the value 0 when it is mutes,
the old value is restored when it is unmuted.
Uses Control Change 7. If your instrument doesn't support this, the
channel won't be muted. (unless you use Filter All/Notes)
@ENDNODE

@NODE FILTNOTES "Filter Notes"
When a channel is muted all note on/off messages will be filtered
out, so you won't hear any music. Program and Control Changes and all
other information will still be send to the instrument.
@ENDNODE

@NODE FILTALL "Filter All"
When a channel is muted all messages will be filtered out, including
the Program and Control Changes.
@ENDNODE

@NODE FILTERS "The Filters"
@{"  Bank Select     " link FILTBANK}
@{"  Program Change  " link FILTPROG}
@ENDNODE

@NODE FILTBANK "Filter Bank Select"
When this option is selected all Bank Select Control Changes
(Control Change Number 0x00 and 0x20) are filtered out.

NOTE: When you're using Midi Play's normal reset, Bank Select and
Program Changes are send when a reset is done. Midi Play send these
messages directly to the midi port. Worse: when you have muted all
channels (what you probabaly did), it still send this information.
To avoid this, set the reset to international. It's not as good as
normal, but works.
@ENDNODE

@NODE FILTPROG "Filter Program Changes"
When this option is selected all Program Changes are filtered out.

NOTE: When you're using Midi Play's normal reset, Bank Select and
Program Changes are send when a reset is done. Midi Play send these
messages directly to the midi port. Worse: when you have muted all
channels (what you probabaly did), it still send this information.
To avoid this, set the reset to international. It's not as good as
normal, but works.
@ENDNODE

@NODE PATCHBAY "The Patch Bay"
In the Patch Bay window you can change all Patch Bay settings.
To create a route from channel A to channel B you must first select
channel A in the In row. Hereafter you can select Channel B in the
Out row.
Removing a route from A to B works the same. Thus, select A in the
In row and then B in the Out row.
@ENDNODE

@NODE PATCHEDIT "The Program editor"
With the program editor you can assign sounds to every channel. First
you have to select your desired instrument from the instrument list.
After that you can select the voice you want.

Some instruments, like my Korg 05R/W, have several banks with sounds. If
you select such an instrument, you must first select in which bank you
want to look.

When you select Groups eightteen groups are presented, from which you
can choose.

General Standard (Roland) intruments have voices with variations. To
select a variation of a voice, first select the voice. After that you
can select a variation by clicking on Variations.

Besides changing the voice you can also change some parameters of the
instruments, like panpot, effect levels and sustain. Every instrument
has its own paramater window. The number of parameters can vary from
a few (the PSS-680 has three) to ten or more (the Korg 05R/W).

When you have two or more instruments connected to the Midi-out of your
Amiga, you have to deselect the instruments manually. For example:
you want to have the Korg 05R/W Piano on Channel 1 and you have a Korg
05R/W :-) and a PSS-680 connected to the Midi-out. Besides selecting
the korg 05R/W Piano you must also change the setup on the Yamaha so
that it won't play notes on Channel 1. Because when you select Piano
on the Korg, Synth Brass will be selected (and played) on the Yamaha.
On the Yamaha you can deselect a channel with the Receive Channel Filter
button and on the Korgs you can set the voices manually to Timbre OFF.

NOTE:
The A bank of the Korg 05R/W and 03R/W contain the default programs in
this program. So if you've changed your programs on your Korg you won't
see it in the Program Select window. However when you select the program
which was replaced by you own program, the program you've created will
be selected. You can change this by editing the Instrument Module of the
instrument. (Only for registered users)

@{" Project Menu  " link PROJECT}
@ENDNODE

@NODE VOICE-LIST "The Voice List"
When you open the Voice List window you can see all voices selected on
every channel. With the Edit buttons (The Gadgets with the channel numbers)
you will enter the @{" Patch Editor " link PATCHEDIT}
@ENDNODE

@NODE MIDI-SETUP "The Midi Setup"
The idea behind this program is the following midi-setup:

    Master Keyboard ------->- Master Midi ------->- Korg 05R/W

In this way you can control the Korg module with the program and play the
sounds on the keyboard. An other setup is the following:

    Master Keyboard --->- Sequencer --->- Master Midi --->- Korg 05R/W

The Sequencer is abled to play notes on all midi channels, so now you
can use the midi mixer properly.

You can also use Master Midi in combination with @{" Midi Play " link MIDI-PLAY}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MIDI-PLAY "Midi Play Support"
You can use Master Midi in combination with Midi Play to get more control
on the played midi-files. Herefore you must first start midiplay and
after that start Master Midi. It will be a little bit tricky when you use
Midi Play v1.1, so I suggest you to use Midi Play v2.0 or higher.

When you want to use things like mute, solo and for much better sound
quality you have to mute all channels in Midi Play. Ohterwise all notes
will be played twice: Midi Play (with no further controls) and Master
Midi both will send all notes to Midi Out. You can change it
permanently by adding/changing this line in the Midi Play tool-types:

    SOLO=0

When you start things up like descibed above the notes played and the
controllers set are visible on you midi-mixer. You can change the programs
etc. now realtime, thus while playing your favorite track, you can also
set your favorite voices. When you have set intruments on every channel,
so can see in the @{" Voice-List " link VOICE-LIST} window which voices are used.
@ENDNODE

@NODE PAST "The past"
25-3-1994 - Version 1.0
    The first version Master Midi.
    Supports:
    - Editor for Korg 05R/W multi-mode;
    - Midi mixer;
    - Patch Bay;

30-3-1994 - Version 1.1
    A few bug fixes:
    - The bank gadgets in the Program Edit window now work properly;
    - The effect edit window is placed to the left, so on screen with
      less than 640 pixels (no overscan) won't bring any problems.
    - The Mute and Solo gadgets will set the level of the Korg to 0,
      so they now work also on the Korg. The buttons do work correctly
      now.

14-4-1994 - Version 1.2
    Added support for:
    - Korg 03R/W
    - General Midi
    - Yamaha PSS-680
    Plus very basic cooperation with Midi Play.

18-5-1994 - Version 2.0
    - Voice-modules
    - Voice-list window
    - Program Change Filter
    - Bank Select Filter
    - Faster Patch Bay implemented
    - Extended functionality of the Mute and Solo buttons
    - Extended support for Midi Play

05-6-1994 - Version 2.0a
    - The Patch Bay now works correctly

12-10-1994 - Version 2.1 beta 1
    - Full Workbench 2.0 support, this means:
   - Fontsize sensitive voices
   - AmigaGuide interactive help
   - Better look
    - Voice groups
    - GS voice variations
    - Loading and saving of registrations in SMF form.
    - Effect modules are now external
    - New look Patch Editor

2-11-1994 - Version 2.1 beta 2
    - NewLook Menus
    - Version support

21-11-1994 - Version 2.1 beta 3
    - NewLook Menus removed
    - Added Volume Control Change for 05R/W

28-11-1994 - Version 2.1 beta 4
    - extra testing

15-12-1994 - Version 2.1 beta 5
    - Control change bug with OS3.1 removed
    - better link for volume control

@ENDNODE

@NODE FUTURE "The future"
I have planned lots of extensions for Master Midi:
    * An AREXX Port
    - A way to control the program completely with your keyboard, fully
      customized (for example change your panning with the pitch bender)
    - Voice Editors
    * Filtering of channels. Like the combination mode of the Korg.
    - Multiple intruments on one channel.
    * More functions for the Patch Bay
    - Keyboard player (like in Deluxe Music)
    - Program Change Map (+ Editor)
    - Configurable slider instead of just volume

    - Editors for lots of other keyboards, synthesizers etc.
      To get this done I need your help. If you have midi implementation
      of an instrument not mentioned in the list @{" About " link ABOUT}
      and you want support for it, contact me!

Extentions marked with * will be introduced in version 2.2, before the
end of 1994!
@ENDNODE

@NODE EXTRAS "Extra's"
At this moment I have finished the following Modules:
    Effect Modules:
   Korg 03R/W
   Korg 05R/W
You can get those modules by registering.

The Korg PC I/F (AG-003) is completed. It is compatible with
Midi Library and so with all programs witch support Midi Library.
Version 2.2 of Master Midi will support the Interface too, with 3
different Patch Bay destinations.
The Korg PC I/F won't be distributed as a part of Master Midi. You can
obtain it by sending the following:
    $5	     Korg PC I/F driver
    $20     Korg PC I/F driver + cable
    $30     Korg PC I/F driver + cable + Master Midi
@ENDNODE
